Abstract
The main dining hall of King Abdulaziz University is the pulse of the university. However, the university restaurant is facing delays and congestion, especially during peak times. The project proposes a web-based application called KAUEssen that will allow students and staff to order their food online to reduce the waiting time. The application will have two different interfaces: the Student Interface and the Restaurant Interface.

Introduction
The university is a fast-paced environment where students have only a few minutes to grab a bite to eat between lectures. The existing system requires the customer to queue twice: once to place the order and a second time to collect the order. This is inefficient and results in the customer missing a meal or reaching the lecture late. The project KAUEats will revolutionize the university restaurant by applying software engineering principles to develop a web-based application that will improve the university restaurant service.
